net.demilich.metastone.game.decks

Class GameDeck

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.demilich.metastone.game.decks.GameDeck
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, Deck
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    RandomDeck

    public class GameDeck
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, Deck
    A deck that contains cards, a name, a hero card, etc. that can be actually used to populate a player's deck in a GameContext.

    Create an instance of this class and add cards using getCards()'s CardList.addCard(String) method. Set the hero class using setHeroClass(HeroClass). Set the format using setFormat(DeckFormat). This format should correspond to the one the GameContext.getDeckFormat() uses.
